title: Auburn WR Duke Williams dismissed from team
text:
WR Duke Williams dismissed from Auburn FOX Sports 
Oct 5, 2015 at 11:46p ET + Shanna Lockwood / USA TODAY Sports FOX Sports Updated Oct 5, 2015 at 11:52p ET 
Sometimes, the talent doesn't outweigh the headache that comes along with it. #Auburn has dismissed Duke Williams. Very talented WR who has had a run of disappointing off field issues. — Bruce Feldman (@BruceFeldmanCFB) October 6, 2015 
Star wide receiver D'haquille "Duke" Williams was kicked off of the Auburn football team on Monday night. The dismissal officially ended Williams' tumultuous time with Gus Malzahn's team. 
According to AuburnSports.com , Williams was involved in an altercation this past weekend at a local nightclub. This only adds to his checkered past at Auburn, which included being suspended for the Outback Bowl in 2014, and another suspension this past August. 
In terms of talent, few match up with Williams' skill-set. During his first year with the Tigers , the Louisiana native had accrued 45 catches for 730 yards and five touchdowns. He was poised to become arguably the top-returning receiver in the SEC this year. However, off-the-field issues derailed a once-promising career. Senior WR Duke Williams has been dismissed from the Auburn football team. Here's a statement from Gus Malzahn pic.twitter.com/3m8ABwLMxZ — WVTM 13 (@WVTM13) October 6, 2015 
Through the first five games of the 2015 season, Williams hauled in 12 passes for 147 yards and one touchdown.
